## Design your website: Test and Colors

Keep web design simple

the main objective of any website is to make it easy for the user to get information he's looking for

Search `Web Design Convention` to learn more about web designing

Web Design Convention - good practices for designers so that their designs can be easily followed 

Web Design convention state that there is always a main button called `call-to-action` or CTA for short in the header, a main title on the page, a logo of the left or in the center of the header, and a social media in the footer

To edit the website, click the Edit button on the top-right side of the page

A panel will have three sections; Blocks, Customize, Theme

Blocks - holds all the different elements we can drag and drop on to our page to create our site

Customize - If you select a block, this section will allows us to customize the block selected 

Theme - Impacts the whole website and not just the block selected. It is here if we want to change fonts

To add Google font, Just click the `Add Google Font` to font dropdown field

You can highlight a text by selecting the text and click `Highlight`

There are some websites that can help you choose your color pallete for you websites like `Color Hunt` or `Adobe Color Wheel`

You can also set the Page layout of the website by editing the `Page Layout` field in Theme section




